<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Another night of Nations League action is upon us with Belgium, Portugal and France all kicking-off their campaigns tonight.</p>

<p>England are currently playing in the early kick-off against Iceland, as Gareth Southgate's side travelled to Reykjavik for their tournament opener. Sportsmail are providing live updates from the Three Lions match.</p>

<p>Elsewhere, in England's group Denmark will host Belgium in the other League A, Group 2 match with Eden Hazard, Kevin De Bruyne and Romelu Lukaku all at Roberto Martinez' disposal.</p>

<p>Portugal face 2018 World Cup finalists Croatia in Group 3, as World Champions France travel to Sweden in the group's other tie.</p>

<p>Here, Sportsmail's IEUAN IVETT will provide all the updates as another night of Nations League action unfolds. </p>

<p>Host commentator</p>

<p>Good evening and welcome to Sportsmail’s coverage for another night of Nations League action. Stay tuned for team news and live updates from all the biggest matches across Europe.</p>
